# PHASE 1: REPOSITORY HYGIENE & SECURITY
# This file ensures that temporary, local, or sensitive files are not 
# committed to the GitHub repository.

# DEPENDENCIES:
# We do not commit 'node_modules/' because they are platform-specific.
# 'npm ci' in the GitHub Actions pipeline reinstalls these from scratch.
node_modules/

# BUILD ARTEFACTS:
# Excludes the compiled JavaScript and source maps. 
# We want the repository to contain only the "Source of Truth" (TypeScript).
dist/
*.js.map

# TEST REPORTS:
# Local test results and Allure reports are generated fresh on every run.
# Committing them would cause "Git Bloat" and unnecessary merge conflicts.
reports/

# SECURITY & ENVIRONMENT:
# Critical: Never commit '.env' files. 
# These may contain local URL overrides or secrets that should remain private.
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# SYSTEM-SPECIFIC FILES:
# Removes "Junk" files created by MacOS or Windows file explorers.
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# IDE CONFIGURATION:
# Excludes settings from editors like VS Code or WebStorm (.idea/).
# This allows different developers to use their own preferred tools.
.idea/
